      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Don't just slather the cream on; use it sparingly, perhaps three times a day, to avoid skin irritation. Taking ibuprofen is fine for managing the pain, but it won't fix the underlying structural issue. Rest is good, but if the pain is intense, you might need a short course of a stronger anti-inflammatory, so consider a 200mg tablet every six hours. Seriously, if you're worried, a quick check-in with an urgent care facility is the smartest move.",
      "source": "target",
